LU-19819: utils: fix 'lctl lfsck_query' usage message

This commit fixes the 'lctl lfsck_query' usage message to correctly
list '-w' as short option for '--wait'

By the way, it also aligns help messages by replacing tabs by space and
have a cleaner output.

Before:
usage: lfsck_start [--device|-M [MDT,OST]_device]
		     [--all|-A] [--create-ostobj|-c [on | off]]
		     [--create-mdtobj|-C [on | off]]
		     [--delay-create-ostobj|-d [on | off]]
		     [--error|-e {continue | abort}] [--help|-h]
		     [--dryrun|-n [on | off]] [--orphan|-o]
		     [--reset|-r] [--speed|-s speed_limit]
		     [--type|-t lfsck_type[,lfsck_type...]]
		     [--window-size|-w size]
After:
lfsck_start: start LFSCK
usage: lfsck_start [--device|-M [MDT,OST]_device]
                   [--all|-A] [--create-ostobj|-c [on | off]]
                   [--create-mdtobj|-C [on | off]]
                   [--delay-create-ostobj|-d [on | off]]
                   [--error|-e {continue | abort}] [--help|-h]
                   [--dryrun|-n [on | off]] [--orphan|-o]
                   [--reset|-r] [--speed|-s speed_limit]
                   [--type|-t lfsck_type[,lfsck_type...]]
                   [--window-size|-w size]

Test-Parameters: trivial
